kerala orphanage rape case: Six held for raping 7 minor inmates of Kerala orphanage 
7-3-2017 
KALPETTA: Six men have been arrested for allegedly raping seven minor inmates of Wayanad Orphange at Muttin in Kalpetta in Wayanad district over the past two months.The police have registered 11 cases against the accused under the Protection of Children from Sexual Offences (Pocso) Act and various IPC sections.The horrid tale of sexual abuse came to light on Monday evening when one of the security guards at the orphanage saw a girl coming out from a shed behind a stationery shop owned by one of the accused, just about 100 metres from the hostel.The police were informed after the hostel staff questioned the girl. The police immediately sent the girls -all in their early teens and students of classes VIII and IX - for medical examination and rape was confirmed. 
